name: AC Side
description:
Training on imagery primarily focused around art by atomic comics. You can get some phenomenal results with really complex prompts but you can also use very simple ones to get some fun and interesting images as well. I would still recommend to use services like Tencent to repair the face a bit.

Making these models can be expensive and very time consuming. If you would consider helping out, it would be much appreciated as any little bit goes a long way

https://www.buymeacoffee.com/Theprotoart

using the regular prompts sometimes results in unexpected outcomes… i’ve tried running it with common prompts, such as manga, comic or vector, anime, etc.

Check out my other models: https://civitai.com/user/mrpbody

modelVersions.name: v2
modelVersions.description:
This model was trained in Dreamlook and uses "openjourney4" as the base model.

Can create some pretty cool characters and decent environments now that it has a lot of mid journey influence with it
